The *repeat-until loop* will execute at least once

<div class="code-block console-wrap">
<div class="code-block code">
<code class="PHP">
counter = 0
repeat
   print(counter)
   counter = counter +1
until counter>10
</code>
</div>
<div  id ="msg1" class="msg">
</div>
<div class="console"></div>
<button class="evalPerl">Run Code!</button>
<ol class="results"></ol> 
</div>


The *break* statement

<div class="code-block console-wrap">
<div class="code-block code">
<code class="PHP">
counter = 0
repeat
   print(counter)
   counter = counter +1
   if counter > 5 then 
      break
   end
until counter>10
</code>
</div>
<div  id ="msg1" class="msg">
</div>
<div class="console"></div>
<button class="evalPerl">Run Code!</button>
<ol class="results"></ol> 
</div>

A common syntax error is to forget the *do* in a *loop* or the *then* in an if statement.


                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      